Certainly! To find the country in Europe with the longest coastline that doesn't border the Atlantic Ocean or the Mediterranean Sea, you can use MATLAB to filter out those countries and then identify the one with the longest coastline. Here's a MATLAB code snippet that performs this task:

```matlab
% List of European countries and their corresponding coastlines in kilometers
country = ["Norway", "Russia", "Turkey", "United Kingdom", "Greece", "Italy", "Spain", "France", "Portugal", "Ireland", "Denmark", "Croatia", "Sweden", "Finland", "Belgium", "Germany", "Netherlands", "Poland", "Estonia", "Latvia", "Lithuania", "Slovenia", "Bulgaria", "Romania", "Ukraine", "Albania", "Montenegro", "Bosnia and Herzegovina", "Serbia", "Macedonia", "Slovakia", "Hungary", "Austria", "Switzerland", "Czech Republic"];
coastline = [25.148, 37.653, 7.200, 17.820, 13.676, 7.600, 4.964, 3.427, 1.793, 1.448, 7.314, 5.835, 3.218, 1.250, 66.5, 2.389, 451.8, 440, 379, 531, 90, 46.6, 354, 225, 2.782, 362, 12.5, 20, 193, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0];

% Countries bordering the Atlantic Ocean or the Mediterranean Sea
atlantic_mediterranean_countries = ["Norway", "United Kingdom", "Ireland", "Portugal", "Spain", "France", "Italy", "Greece", "Turkey", "Albania", "Montenegro", "Slovenia", "Croatia"];

% Logical index for countries that do not border the Atlantic or the Mediterranean
not_atlantic_mediterranean = ~ismember(country, atlantic_mediterranean_countries);

% Filtered list of countries and their coastlines
filtered_countries = country(not_atlantic_mediterranean);
filtered_coastlines = coastline(not_atlantic_mediterranean);

% Find the index of the country with the longest coastline
[~, idx] = max(filtered_coastlines);

% Find the country with the longest coastline
country_with_longest_coastline = filtered_countries(idx);
longest_coastline = filtered_coastlines(idx);

% Display the result
fprintf('The country in Europe with the longest coastline that does not border the Atlantic Ocean or the Mediterranean Sea is %s with a coastline of %.3f kilometers.\n', country_with_longest_coastline, longest_coastline);
```

This MATLAB script first filters out the countries that border the Atlantic or the Mediterranean Sea using the `ismember` function. Then, it finds the country with the longest coastline from the remaining list using the `max` function. Finally, it displays the result.
